      "timestamp": "2026-05-19T14:38:04.335Z",
      "text": "BSE replacing Wipro in Nifty 50 — It is rare but possible. Criteria is based on free float market cap but it also looks at average data over past 6 months or so. On top index is reviewed only once in 6 month. So that is like a year of gap. So normally a rising stock would enter NN50 first and then N50, but in rare situation, where stock has a strong bull run in short period (like BSE did), chances are that during last review it didn’t qualify for N100 and when next review comes it has already surpassed NN50 threshold and might be in N50 range already.",
